================
description
================

1) This program accept file name from user and open that file in default mode(Read).
2) Required filename will be taken from command line

================
about the code
================

	input	:	file name, file_mode	[for more, see NOTES]
	output	:	result - file descripter
 			
=============
How to run
=============

	make	:	compile the code and generates executable file as "myexe"
	make run:	run the executable with command line argument
			for this you have to pass parameter as: 
			
			$ make run p1="parameter_value1" p2="parameter_value2"
	
=============
NOTES
=============

	1) file_mode : it could be-
				   i)	read
				   ii)	write
				   iii)	read_write
				   iv)	create
				   v)	truncate

	2)If the given file is unable to open, it will display the appropriate reason.
	3)If the given file is not present in working directory, it will create a new file with the provided name.
	
